# v3 re-benchmark audit (benchmarks/audit/) — commit the AGGREGATE results
# (JSON + aggregate CSVs: confusion / per-class / thresholds / calibration /
# subgroups / icd summary / backend comparison / parser cost), but NEVER the
# patient-level per-case CSVs (MIMIC DUA: they carry generated narratives +
# stay_ids). The global `*.csv` rule above hides every CSV; re-include the safe
# aggregate ones under the audit tree, then re-exclude the per-case files.
!benchmarks/audit/**/*.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/per_case_master.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/parser_audit.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/triage_acuity.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/disposition.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/doctor_diagnosis.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/doctor_department.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/exact_icd.csv
benchmarks/audit/**/backend_comparison_parser_per_case.csv

